The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Kochi, Jan. 7 (PTI): A Swedish couple was attacked with a knife by a drunk man at the Thekkady Periyar reserve in Kerala yesterday.

 Coaster suffered injuries on his arms and neck while his wife Evas right eye was pierced by the knife. 

 A doctor at the hospital where Eva is admitted said a CT scan showed that her optic nerve had been cut and she could lose her vision. 

 The accused has been arrested. 

 New Delhi (PTI): The New Year has in store more work and less play, with many festivals that are public holidays falling on weekends. As many as 19 of the 50 public and restricted holidays fall on Saturdays and Sundays, according to the list of holidays released by the ministry of personnel.

 Junagadh (PTI): Two persons, one of them a boy, were mauled by a lion in a village here on Sunday, forest department officials said. Four lions are reported to have entered the village in the morning. 

 New Delhi (PTI): Broadcast regulator Trai will send a team to CAS-notified areas of Delhi, Mumbai and Calcutta to take stock of the new cable TV delivery system in these metros. 

 Trai met with cable operators on Friday regarding CAS problems.




